ANTHRAX, HUMAN - GREECE (NORTHWEST)
***********************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Fri, 19 Oct 2001 20:22:06 -0400
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Xinhua News Agency [edited]

Case of Anthrax Disease Reported in Greece
------------------------------------------
ATHENS, Oct 19, 2001 (Xinhua via COMTEX) -- A cattle herder in Kozani,
northwestern Greece, was diagnosed with anthrax disease on Friday, the
semi-official Athens News Agency reported from northern city of Salonika.
The herder, whose name was not released, contracted the disease from his
herd. The victim was taken to a Salonika hospital, when he had shown
symptoms of the disease.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Livestock anthrax is enzootic in Greece. Presumably he became infected
when skinning and butchering a contaminated carcass. - Mod.MHJ]
